infodynamics.measures.continuous
Interface MutualInfoCalculatorMultiVariate

All Superinterfaces:
ChannelCalculatorCommon, ChannelCalculatorMultiVariate
All Known Subinterfaces:
MutualInfoCalculatorMultiVariateWithMarginals
All Known Implementing Classes:
MutualInfoCalculatorMultiVariateGaussian, MutualInfoCalculatorMultiVariateKernel, MutualInfoCalculatorMultiVariateKraskov, MutualInfoCalculatorMultiVariateKraskov1, MutualInfoCalculatorMultiVariateKraskov2, MutualInfoCalculatorMultiVariateKraskovByMulti, MutualInfoCalculatorMultiVariateKraskovByMulti1, MutualInfoCalculatorMultiVariateKraskovByMulti2, MutualInfoMultiVariateCommon
public interface MutualInfoCalculatorMultiVariate
extends ChannelCalculatorMultiVariate

Interface for multivariate implementations of the mutual information.

Intended usage of the child classes:

  1. Construct
  2. Set properties using ChannelCalculatorCommon.setProperty(String, String)
  3. ChannelCalculatorMultiVariate.initialise(int, int) or #initialise(int, int, double)
  4. Provide the observations to the calculator using: ChannelCalculatorMultiVariate.setObservations(double[][], double[][]), or #setCovariance(double[][]), or a sequence of: ChannelCalculatorCommon.startAddObservations(), multiple calls to either ChannelCalculatorMultiVariate.addObservations(double[][], double[][]) or ChannelCalculatorMultiVariate.addObservations(double[][], double[][], int, int), and then ChannelCalculatorCommon.finaliseAddObservations().
  5. Compute the required information-theoretic results, primarily: ChannelCalculatorCommon.computeAverageLocalOfObservations() to return the average value based on the supplied observations; or other calls to compute local values or statistical significance.

Author:
Joseph Lizier, joseph.lizier at gmail.com
See Also:
"T. M. Cover and J. A. Thomas, 'Elements of Information Theory' (John Wiley & Sons, New York, 1991)."
